The paper deals with the problem of place recognition for mobile robots, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also leverages computer vision techniques to improve place recognition, specifically using semantic place categorization (cs.CV). The use of machine learning and deep learning techniques to improve performance also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also involves natural language processing techniques to segment physical space, which could potentially fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
